  # notes

  Container life cycle 
==============
Every container will get one ip add.

	1. docker create :- it will create only container 
	2. docker start :- it will start the container
	3. docker inspect :- it will give all details of container
	4. Curl :- to check svc response 
	5. docker logs :- it will give logs of the container
	6. docker stop :- it will stop the container 
   docker restart :- it will restart container
   docker exec -it :- it will login to the container
   	9. docker run :- firstly it will pull the image , secondly it will create the container, thirdly it will start the container.
	10. docker ps :- to list only running containers
	11. docker ps -a:- to list all containers.
	12. docker pause :- it will pause the container (means stops only container process)
	13. docker unpause :- it will unpause the container.
	14. docker rm ;- To delete only stopped containers
	15. docker rm -f :- To delete running containers directly.
	16. docker rmi ;- to delete unused images
	17. docker rmi $(docker images -q) :- To delete all images 
	18. docker rm $(docker ps -aq):- to delete all stopped containers
docker rm -f $(docker ps -aq) :- To delete all containers including running.
